f=Cybersecurity/bastion/custom/cloud-posture/SKILL.md · in=Detecting misconfigurations business's cloud accounts before attacker public storage buckets, open security groups, over-permissive IAM policies, unencrypted volumes, disabled logging. bastion **detects specs fix**; operator (or ops through normal gate) remediates bastion holds cloud keys (the security-inversion). · p=overwhelming majority cloud breaches misconfigurations, exploits public bucket, database open internet, IAM role everything. CSPM continuously checks cloud's configuration against secure baselines found fixed routine, discovered breach report. · wu=cloud account exists (per stack-profile's hosting)., "Is our cloud secure," "check misconfigs," "public bucket," "open port," "over-permissive role.", Posture scan cadence; after any infra change. · st:/ Protocol=INVENTORY (the cloud accounts/resources stack-profile hosting) CHECK against baselines (CIS Benchmarks provider security best-practices: storage public, security groups least-open, IAM least-privilege, encryption on, logging/audit-trail enabled, MFA root/org) PRIORITIZE (findings exposure data-sensitivity public bucket PII outranks dev misconfig) SPEC FIX (bastion writes remediation; operator ops-through-the-gate applies bastion doesn't hold cloud admin) RISK (findings warden's register; over-permissive cloud IAM flags keyring's doctrine) RE-CHECK (drift: fixed misconfig reappears finding). · in=**Check against real baselines.** CIS Benchmarks cloud provider's security best-practices opinion. GRC CIS Controls pack (Sushegaad) reference catalog; provider docs dated (like ops's playbooks cloud services change). **The classic misconfigs first.** Public storage, internet-open databases/ports, over-permissive IAM, encryption rest, disabled audit logging, root/org accounts without MFA breach headlines; check them scan. **Prioritize exposure data sensitivity.** public bucket holding customer PII (veil's classification) critical; misconfig empty dev infra low. Risk-based, raw-count. **bastion detects specs; operator/ops remediates.** bastion writes exact fix; applying cloud account goes through operator ops's normal deploy gate bastion holds cloud admin credentials (the inversion; cloud IAM ultimate blast radius). **Findings register risks.** misconfig scores warden's register; over-permissive cloud IAM least-privilege failure keyring's doctrine covers (cloud identity human identity seam). **Watch drift.** remediated misconfig reappears means process gap (IaC updated, manual change) that's finding, re-fix. · of=`## Cloud Posture: [account] — baseline: [CIS + provider] \· Findings: [misconfig \· resource \· exposure \· data-sensitivity \· severity] \· Classic checks: [public storage \· open SG/ports \· IAM least-priv \· encryption \· logging \· root MFA] \· Fix spec → [operator / ops gate] (bastion detects, doesn't apply) \· Risks → warden register \· over-permissive cloud IAM → keyring doctrine \· drift flags` · pr=**Check against real baselines** (CIS provider), dated, opinion., **The classic misconfigs breach headlines** check them scan., **Prioritize exposure data sensitivity** risk-based, raw count., **bastion detects specs; operator/ops remediates** cloud keys (the inversion)., **Findings register risks; drift finding.** · f=CSPM tooling manual checks against CIS Benchmark provider, prioritized classic high-blast misconfigs, labeled manual; recommend CSPM connector operator., Multi-cloud one baseline provider; shared findings (public storage, IAM) factored; seams between clouds extra attack surface, flagged. · b:with Other Skills=**hardening-baselines** (sibling): host/OS/endpoint config; cloud control-plane config., **network-security** (sibling): security groups/segmentation overlap cloud misconfigs found here, network policy designed there., **keyring**: over-permissive cloud IAM least-privilege failure (cloud identity seam)., **ops (Engineering)**: remediation ships through ops's gate; ops's maintenance-hygiene patches, bastion checks config., **veil**: data-sensitivity what misconfigured resource exposes comes veil's classification., **warden**: findings register risks.